from langchain.vectorstores import Chroma
from langchain.embeddings.openai import OpenAIEmbeddings
persist_directory = 'docs/chroma/'

vectordb = Chroma(persist_directory=persist_directory, 
                  embedding_function=embedding)

Prompt

In[15]:
from langchain.prompts import PromptTemplate

# Build prompt
template = """Use the following pieces of context to answer the question at the end. If you don't know the answer, just say that you don't know, don't try to make up an answer. Use three sentences maximum. Keep the answer as concise as possible. Always say "thanks for asking!" at the end of the answer. 
{context}
Question: {question}
Helpful Answer:"""
QA_CHAIN_PROMPT = PromptTemplate.from_template(template)
In[16]:
# Inspect the prompt used in the chain
print(QA_CHAIN_PROMPT, "\n\n#####\n\n", type(QA_CHAIN_PROMPT))

Always say "thanks for asking!" at the end of the answer. \n{context}\nQuestion: {question}\nHelpful Answer:' template_format='f-string' validate_template=True

qa_chain = RetrievalQA.from_chain_type(
    llm,
    retriever=vectordb.as_retriever(),
    return_source_documents=True,
    chain_type_kwargs={"prompt": QA_CHAIN_PROMPT}
)

RetrievalQA limitations

QA fails to preserve conversational history.

In[34]:
qa_chain = RetrievalQA.from_chain_type(
    llm,
    retriever=vectordb.as_retriever()
)
In[35]:
question = "Is probability a class topic?"
result = qa_chain({"query": question})
result["result"]
Out[35]:
'Yes, probability is a class topic in the course being described. The instructor assumes familiarity with basic probability and statistics.'

This question is posed as "StuffDocuments" chain

Here, all the context was shared with an LLM in a single session, this strategy is not very scalable as LLM context windows are limited which limits the amount of information they can handle for 1 query.

In the image below, note how all in the StuffDocuments call the context and metadata is all passed to the LLM with the final question, LLM returns the answer in a single pass

In[37]:
question = "why are those prerequesites needed?"
result = qa_chain({"query": question})
result["result"]
Out[37]:
'The prerequisites for the class are needed because the course assumes that all students have a basic knowledge of computer science and computer skills. This foundational knowledge is essential for understanding the concepts and techniques taught in the class, such as big-O notation and basic computer principles.'

The above question was posed as a "StuffDocuments chain"

Here, all the context was shared with an LLM in a single session, this strategy is not very scalable as LLM context windows are limited which limits the amount of information they can handle for 1 query.

In the image below, note how all the context is bunched together in one call, we get our answer from a single call which leads to good response time but limits amount of context that can be shared

Note, The LLM response varies. Some responses do include a reference to probability which might be gleaned from referenced documents. The point is simply that the model does not have access to past questions or answers, this will be covered in the next section.
